nicolas mirzayantz executive profile  biography  bloomberg july    pm et chemicals company overview of international flavors  fragrances inc snapshotpeople  overviewboard memberscommittees executive profile nicolas mirzayantz group president of fragrances international flavors  fragrances incagetotal calculated compensationthis person is connected to  board members in  different organizations across  different industriessee board relationshipsas of fiscal year  background mr nicolas mirzayantz has been the group president of fragrances at international flavors  fragrances inc since january  in this role mr mirzayantz is responsible for global strategy commercial and creative execution people development and profit and loss in the fragrances business unit mr mirzayantz serves as president of iff’s prestigious unit of natural products laboratoire monique rémy in grasse france he has extensive experience in the creation  and sales of fine fragrances mr mirzayantz served as secretary of research institute for fragrance materials inc he served as senior vice president of fine fragrance and beauty care of international flavors  fragrances inc since october  until february  and was its member temporary office of the ceo from october   to february  he was responsible for iff’s global fine fragrances group including beauty care as well as the general management of the business development and operations activities in north america including flavors and functional fragrances additionally he oversaw the integration and development of iff’s creative centers in new york and paris he served as a vice president of global business development for fine fragrance and toiletries at international flavors  fragrances inc since december  until september  and served as its regional manager of north american region since april  mr mirzayantz served as vice president global business development of fine fragrances and toiletries since january  fragrances general manager of iff france from january  to january  and also served as vice president of commercial and creative director of iff france mr mirzayantz joined iff’s creative center in paris in  and has held increasingly responsible positions during his more than year career with the company he oversaw iffs creative centers in new york and paris as well as its prestigious unit of natural products laboratoire monique rémy in grasse france at iff he was in charge of integrating the new york and paris creative centers to reflect its global strategy in its fine fragrance business he joined iff france in  as a member of the sales team and held increasingly senior positions as part of iffs fine fragrance account team prior to his appointment as commercial and creative director in france he spent four years as vice president global account manager for estée lauder based in new york prior to iff he served as deputy trade commissioner at the french embassy in nicaragua in  and  he serves as vice chairman of the board of directors and director at research institute for fragrance materials inc he is vice chair industry advisory board for the fashion institute of technology fit master’s program he serves on the board of the international fragrance association ifra mr mirzayantz holds a baccalauréat degree in economics and a master of economics degree from the university of paris ii assas he also completed the international executive program at insead in fontainebleau in read full background corporate headquarters  west th streetnew york new york united statesphone fax  board members memberships vice chairresearch institute for fragrance materials inc education bachelors degree université panthéonassas  paris iimasters degree université panthéonassas  paris ii other affiliations université panthéonassas  paris iiresearch institute for fragrance materials inc annual compensation salarytotal annual compensation stocks options restricted stock awardsall other compensation total compensation total annual cash compensa